        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 9 at 3:47AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 347 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Abbeville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Abbeville and Due West.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
